					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-443884#post-1858469</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-443884/scp-1049#post-1858469</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 25 Sep 2013 16:52:34 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1472934</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>When the picture first loaded and I saw the eyes, I couldn't help but exclaim &quot;Whoa!&quot; out loud. I saw the +39 rating and wondered how an SCP article with <em>that picture</em> could be so relatively low-rated.</p> <p>Unfortunately, the article was incredibly underwhelming, especially in comparison to the picture. I'm not saying it's a bad idea or even a boring one, but…something about the way it's done just fails to hook me. I can't quite put my finger on why I'm hesitant to upvote this (mind you, I'm <em>very</em> generous with my upvotes)…I can't pick out a particular thing that's poor in either concept or execution, but it's just…blah. Sorry. I wish I could provide helpful feedback, but that's all I've got. :(</p> <p>…On second thought, +1 anyway because I can't figure out why not. Still…</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
