				<wikidot:authorName>Pig_catapult</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>233556</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Brain hitting the ground would probably be the big one, followed by inability to inflate the lungs. If both of those things were compensated for, the victim would still probably die of shock and internal bleeding. Were all that somehow avoided, however, their ultimate cause of death would be anemia, because they have no bone marrow with which to produce new blood cells.</p> 
				 	]]>
